  "response": "Snakes may eat baby chickens because they are opportunistic feeders and will consume prey that is readily available and easy to catch. Baby chickens are small, vulnerable, and often unable to defend themselves effectively against predators like snakes. Additionally, baby chickens provide a good source of nutrition for snakes, which need to eat to maintain their energy levels and support their growth and reproduction.",
